As presented in Proposition 3, when user i only considers the seen beneÔ¨Åt, i.e., vi = 1, the social beneÔ¨Åt bi j(S) becomes independent with j and is always one under strategy S. This illustrates the situation where a user uses social networks for disseminating information and does not care about the responses received from the information receivers. Her social requirement is fully satisÔ¨Åed as long as the selected information receiver j receives it, and her social beneÔ¨Åt increases as the number of receivers (i.e., the size of N) increases.

